&gt; Some parts of the DNS are well maintained, and others not so. And some
&gt; are not set up very well (e.g. lack of adequate secondary servers). I
&gt; feel that a program could be written to look around the DNS (using
&gt; zone transfer mostly) and detect inconsistencies and infelicities. I
&gt; am sure this would be well worth while in Australia at the moment. I
&gt; believe that David Hornsby from the University of Melbourne has had a
&gt; bit of a look into how hard this would be and he might like to comment.

If you are interested, I have a program that reads a database file and 
verifies that the name servers listed in the NS records *are* authoritative 
servers for that domain.  We use this program within HP to detect 
inconsistencies in our data or servers that need to be fixed.  I have 
provided the NIC with a copy, but I don't know if they are using it.  The 
routines that parse the data files are from BIND.  My code does the checking 
when it sees an NS record.   

paul

